scene.message:
Maki: I don't think we really{nl}
need TV or radio anyway. Is{nl}
that such a big deal?{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: The only thing you can{nl}
trust is your own strength...{nl}
A sound way of thinking.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: I, too, wish to unravel{nl}
this mystery with my own{nl}
hands.{waitkey}{clearbox}It's a chance to put all I've{nl}
learned to good use, after{nl}
all.{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: We go from the factory{nl}
to SEBEC, right? Then we beat{nl}
Kandori, right?{waitkey}{clearbox}And then it's all solved,{nl}
and I'm the hero!{wait_fr:21}{nl}
That's how it goes, yeah?{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: Kandori... I guess we{nl}
really do have to go after{nl}
him, huh...{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: TV and radio both{nl}
being out — does that mean{nl}
some kind of signal trouble?{waitkey}{clearbox}Why would something like{nl}
that happen?{waitkey}{ret}

Customer: The TV and radio{nl}
are both dead, and my parents{nl}
are cowering under the{nl}
covers...{waitkey}{clearbox}In the end, you've just got{nl}
to sort things out yourself.{waitkey}{ret}

Shopkeeper: That's my private{nl}
room over there~ So you're{nl}
not allowed in, okay~{waitkey}{ret}

Shopkeeper: I'm not the least{nl}
bit scared of demons, no~{waitkey}{clearbox}Those things are bound to be{nl}
a trick of the eye or some{nl}
kind of hoax!{waitkey}{ret}
